data.author: Ginger
data.text:
So, today is a day of celebration! But we’re always thinking of what work comes next. 

With the Framework, Authority, & the Fund now all agreed, what comes next is the implementation. The @firstpeoplesvic will hold fresh elections so community can vote for their representatives. https://t.co/pdZGfNQXq4

data.author: Ginger
data.text:
Each phase of the Victorian Treaty process has built upon the last. 
Centuries of resistance & activism, staunch Elders, the civil rights movement, to the Aboriginal Treaty Working Group, Vic Treaty Advancement Commissioner, & the democratically elected Assembly. @firstpeoplesvic https://t.co/0asOhcSTXL
data.clean_text: Each phase of the Victorian Treaty process has built upon the last Centuries of resistance activism staunch Elders the civil rights movement to the Aboriginal Treaty Working Group Vic Treaty Advancement Commissioner the democratically elected Assembly

data.author: Ginger
data.text:
Victoria is genuinely leading the way. 

Victoria is the only jurisdiction in Australia progressing the 3 elements called for in the Uluṟu Statement From The Heart: Voice, Treaty and Truth. It’s a testimony to the Aboriginal communities who just keep fighting. @firstpeoplesvic https://t.co/q74FpkapWb
data.clean_text: Victoria is genuinely leading the way Victoria is the only jurisdiction in Australia progressing the 3 elements called for in the Ulu u Statement From The Heart Voice Treaty and Truth It s a testimony to the Aboriginal communities who just keep fighting

data.author: Ginger
data.text:
The stage is set for Treaties to be developed in Victoria. 

Traditional Owner Treaties at the local level will be designed and negotiated by Traditional Owner groups, in addition to an overarching statewide Treaty to secure meaningful structural reforms. @firstpeoplesvic https://t.co/btmF7R4rVQ
data.clean_text: The stage is set for Treaties to be developed in Victoria Traditional Owner Treaties at the local level will be designed and negotiated by Traditional Owner groups in addition to an overarching statewide Treaty to secure meaningful structural reforms

data.author: Ginger
data.text:
Importantly, the Treaty Negotiation Framework was finalised and signed today, on Wurundjeri Woi Wurrung Country. 

The Framework adopts the principles of the @UN Declaration on the Rights of Indigenous Peoples. It ensures that no groups will be left behind. @firstpeoplesvic https://t.co/ip4S8H5tNx
data.clean_text: Importantly the Treaty Negotiation Framework was finalised and signed today on Wurundjeri Woi Wurrung Country The Framework adopts the principles of the Declaration on the Rights of Indigenous Peoples It ensures that no groups will be left behind

data.author: Ginger
data.text:
The Self-Determination Fund will drive First Peoples’ wealth and prosperity, long-term. 

And in the shorter term, will assist Traditional Owner nations and groups across Victoria to get ‘Treaty-ready’. @firstpeoplesvic https://t.co/vvSbirPU4H
data.clean_text: The Self Determination Fund will drive First Peoples wealth and prosperity long term And in the shorter term will assist Traditional Owner nations and groups across Victoria to get Treaty ready

data.author: Ginger
data.text:
The Treaty Authority will be the independent ‘umpire’ for the process going forward. It’s grounded in Aboriginal Lore, law, and culture. 
The Authority will not be subject to Ministerial direction, nor subject to the insecure funding arrangements of the past. @firstpeoplesvic https://t.co/VxswrER70A
data.clean_text: The Treaty Authority will be the independent umpire for the process going forward It s grounded in Aboriginal Lore law and culture The Authority will not be subject to Ministerial direction nor subject to the insecure funding arrangements of the past

data.author: Ginger
data.text:
Today’s signing ceremony by the banks of the Birrarung means that all three pieces of crucial Treaty architecture are in place.

The First Peoples’ Assembly and the Victorian Government have negotiated for years to bring about this milestone. @firstpeoplesvic https://t.co/Z2wsJElRAy
data.clean_text: Today s signing ceremony by the banks of the Birrarung means that all three pieces of crucial Treaty architecture are in place The First Peoples Assembly and the Victorian Government have negotiated for years to bring about this milestone

data.author: Ginger
data.text: Absolutely huge announcement today at the First Peoples’ Assembly of Victoria. This is the biggest change of a generation. The stage is set for Treaty-making in Victoria, in a process designed and led by Aboriginal communities and Traditional Owners of Country. @firstpeoplesvic https://t.co/0oiHcX3psh
data.clean_text: Absolutely huge announcement today at the First Peoples Assembly of Victoria This is the biggest change of a generation The stage is set for Treaty making in Victoria in a process designed and led by Aboriginal communities and Traditional Owners of Country
